doc.fast.ai

Documentation on models to pass into `vision_learner`: timm.fast.ai 

**DataBlock** is a high level API to quickly get your data in a DataLoaders.  
There are more domain-specific blocks (TransformBlock, CategoryBlock, RegressionBlock). 
DataBlock is the General API for quickly building Datasets and DataLoaders. 

**Understanding the DataBlock block parameter:**

*ImageBlock* Loads an image file, converts it to a PILImage (or TensorImage) and prepares 
it for image-specific augmentations and normalization.  

*CategoryBlock* Takes the label (here a string obtained from the parent folder), maps 
each distinct label to an integer index, and produces a categorical target tensor.

Without ImageBlock the pipeline would treat the imput as a generic object.
Without CategoryBlock the target would remain a raw string wich cannot be used directly by a 
loss function.

Fastai requires that you set aside data for **validation** with the *splitter* 
parameter of the DataBlock.  

"Fine-tuning" a model means that we're starting with a model someone else has trained using some other dataset (called the pretrained model), and adjusting the weights a little bit so that the model learns to recognise your particular dataset. In this case, the pretrained model was trained to recognise photos in imagenet, and widely-used computer vision dataset with images covering 1000 categories)

**Segmentation** in AI refers to a computer vision technique that analyzes an image at the pixel level to identify objects and their exact boundaries. Instead of just placing a rough bounding box around an object, AI models generate a detailed "mask" that outlines the shape, allowing machines to understand an image comprehensively


